Meet S6 artist @lukegram 📸 

Luke is an accomplished Canadian travel photographer whose work has gained recognition for its exceptional quality. He has a diverse portfolio that encompasses various styles, including portraits, landscapes, architecture, and astrophotography. His art has been featured in publications such as Gestalaten, Daily Mail, and Reuters, and he’s also collaborated with commercial brands such as Adobe, Uber, IKEA, and more.

Speaking on creative inspiration, Luke says, “I think the best way to explain what inspires me creatively is to look back at where it started for me.
​
​When I was a kid I used to sit in my parents basement and read their growing pile of Nat Geo’s. Over the years I built a sort of mental map of the world. The awesome peaks of the Himalayas. The frozen world of Antarctic. The golden deserts of Wadi Rum. I began to romanticize what laid outside of my quiet southern Ontario suburb.
​
​So finally when I could, I started going to see these places for myself, and they were far more incredible then I had dreamed up in my parents basement. And on these journeys, sometimes months long, I was fortunate to meet incredible people. And I realized that I hadn’t romanticized the world - it really, truly is this incredible of a place.
​
​And so I want to share that, and capture that. To show people what an amazing place we are able to call our planet.””

Luke’s photographs are a stunning visual journey that celebrates the beauty and diversity of our world. His art captures the essence of the places he’s visited, the people he’s met, and the cultures he’s experienced. He hopes to inspire viewers to develop a deeper appreciation for the world and all it has to offer. With a keen eye for detail and a talent for bringing out the best in his subjects, Luke’s photography is a true reflection of his passion and expertise.”

See even more from @lukegram on Society6.com!

I am honoured to have been awarded 1st place in @iphotoawards Travel category with my series “6 days and 5 nights in North Korea”.

Turns out sneaking that SD card out in my sock was worth all the risk 🧦💾🚨🚔

Discover the entire series: https://www.photoawards.com/winner/zoom.php?eid=8-1682172450-23

“This series provides a candid glimpse into the lives of the people and the culture of North Korea, a country shrouded in mystery and contradiction. Through my lens, I aimed to capture the everyday realities of the locals in Kaesong, Pyongyang, and Nampo, while also delicately unmasking the Potemkin aspect of our exposure. My photography series presents an honest and unfiltered view of North Korea, capturing the warmth and resilience of its people, while also revealing the stark contrast between the carefully curated image and the reality on the ground.”
